<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-04-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-04-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="1527" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1527">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.41/369.</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to Consul <persName type="to">Letcher</persName></hi>.</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left">No. 350.]</seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-04-06">
                                        <hi rend="italic">April 6, 1915</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The Department has received your
                                despatch No. 601 of March 25, 1915, reporting that certain portions
                                of the ranch [etc.]</p>
                            <p>You are instructed to inform Mr. Harvie that the matter should be
                                taken up with the British Vice Consul.</p>
                            <p>If so requested, you may cooperate with the British representative to
                                obtain relief for Mrs. Benton.</p>
                            <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                            <closer>For the Secretary of State: <lb/>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilbur J. Carr.</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>